Example 13

Over 4 consecutive years, the value of a house increases by 15%, increases by 9%, decreases by 4%, and increases by 18%. What is the overall percentage increase in value over this period?

Solution:

Let $\$x$ be the original value.

$\therefore$ value after 1 year $= \$x \times 1.15$ {15% increase}
$\therefore$ value after 2 years $= \$x \times 1.15 \times 1.09$ {9% increase}
$\therefore$ value after 3 years $= \$x \times 1.15 \times 1.09 \times 0.96$ {4% decrease}
$\therefore$ value after 4 years $= \$x \times 1.15 \times 1.09 \times 0.96 \times 1.18$ {18% increase}
$\approx \$x \times 1.4200$

$\therefore$ a 42% increase in the value has occurred.
